.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[\fIfile\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from
standard input and executes them. It handles
the \fIPATH\fR environment variable, allowing commands to be run
without specifying their full path.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support command-line options.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with code n (0 by default). Numeric argument required.
.TP
.B env
Print all environment variables. If SHLVL is not set, prints SHLVL=0.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run the shell in interactive mode:
.B hsh
.TP
Run a command without specifying the full path:
.B ls

.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
0
Success
.TP
126
Error in child process execution
.TP
127
Command not found
.TP
2
Numeric argument required for exit
.TP
N
Exit status of executed command

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run the shell interactively:
.B hsh
.TP
Run a command without specifying full path:
.B ls -l
.TP
Check exit status:
.B exit 42
echo $?

.SH ENVIRONMENT
Uses \fIPATH\fR to locate executables

.SH AUTHORS
Lucas Podevin, Tommy Jouhans

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)
